Portugal is set to build the world's largest solar energy power station in Alentejo, creating 240 jobs.
The plant will have 350,000 solar panels spread over 114 hectares near Moura, producing 62 megawatts.
Meanwhile, a solar-powered car race in Australia saw a Dutch team win for the third time.
In the Philippines, a solar power project will provide electricity to rural households and schools.
Taiwan aims to be a top solar energy firm by 2008.
Solar energy is gaining traction, with companies like Clear Blue Hawaii and Voltaic Systems producing innovative products.
Italy even unveiled Europe's first solar-powered train
